#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.51"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.51:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.51:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "6. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.51:0.3"
msgid "51. Paṭhamadvebrāhmaṇasutta"
msgstr "51. Two Brahmins (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.51:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dve brāhmaṇā jiṇṇā vuddhā mahallakā addhagatā vayoanuppattā "
"vīsavassasatikā jātiyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then two old brahmins—elderly and senior, who were advanced in years and had "
"reached the final stage of life, a hundred and twenty years old—went up to "
"the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "an3.51:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te brāhmaṇā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side, and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an3.51:1.3"
msgid ""
"“mayamassu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā jiṇṇā vuddhā mahallakā addhagatā "
"vayoanuppattā vīsavassasatikā jātiyā;"
msgstr ""
"“We brahmins, Master Gotama, are old, elderly and senior, we’re advanced in "
"years and have reached the final stage of life; we’re a hundred and twenty "
"years old."

msgctxt "an3.51:1.4"
msgid "te camhā akatakalyāṇā akatakusalā akatabhīruttāṇā."
msgstr ""
"And we haven’t done what is good and skillful, nor have we made a shelter "
"from fear."

msgctxt "an3.51:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ovadatu no bhavaṃ gotamo, anusāsatu no bhavaṃ gotamo yaṃ amhākaṃ assa "
"dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Advise us, Master Gotama, instruct us! It will be for our lasting welfare "
"and happiness.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.51:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Taggha tumhe, brāhmaṇā, jiṇṇā vuddhā mahallakā addhagatā vayoanuppattā "
"vīsavassasatikā jātiyā;"
msgstr "“Indeed, brahmins, you’re old, elderly and senior."

msgctxt "an3.51:2.2"
msgid "te cattha akatakalyāṇā akatakusalā akatabhīruttāṇā."
msgstr ""
"And you haven’t done what is good and skillful, nor have you made a shelter "
"from fear."

msgctxt "an3.51:2.3"
msgid "Upanīyati kho ayaṃ, brāhmaṇā, loko jarāya byādhinā maraṇena."
msgstr "This world is led on by old age, sickness, and death."

# BB has “support” for parayana. It does indeed mean that at AN 3.36, etc. But here it must be a synonym of the other terms.
msgctxt "an3.51:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ upanīyamāne kho, brāhmaṇā, loke jarāya byādhinā maraṇena, yo idha "
"kāyena saṃyamo vācāya saṃyamo manasā saṃyamo, taṃ tassa petassa tāṇañca "
"leṇañca dīpañca saraṇañca parāyaṇañcāti."
msgstr ""
"But restraint here by way of body, speech, and mind is the shelter, "
"protection, island, refuge, and haven for the departed.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.1"
msgid "Upanīyati jīvitamappamāyu,"
msgstr "“This life, so very short, is led onward."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.2"
msgid "Jarūpanītassa na santi tāṇā;"
msgstr "There’s no shelter for someone who’s been led on by old age."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.3"
msgid "Etaṃ bhayaṃ maraṇe pekkhamāno,"
msgstr "Seeing this peril in death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.4"
msgid "Puññāni kayirātha sukhāvahāni."
msgstr "you should do good deeds that bring happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.1"
msgid "Yodha kāyena saṃyamo,"
msgstr "The restraint practiced here—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.2"
msgid "Vācāya uda cetasā;"
msgstr "of body, speech, and mind—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ tassa petassa sukhāya hoti,"
msgstr "leads the departed to happiness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.4"
msgid "Yaṃ jīvamāno pakaroti puññan”ti."
msgstr "as the good deeds done while living.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.51:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
